    "attributes": {
        "action": "Stop local borough councils charging for replacement recycling bins",
        "additional_details": "South Ribble Borough Council charge \u00a330 for a replacement wheelie bin or \u00a310 for a replacement paper recycling bin, which may have been lost or damaged (blown away) or stolen, through no fault of the resident.",
        "background": "The UK Government has a target to recycle 50% of all household waste by 2020.  A recent report showed that we recycled less in 2016-17 than in 2011-12.  Is there any wonder that the general public is recycling less when local borough councils are imposing charges on residents for replacement bins.",
